        <body>
      
		<pb n="1"/>
			<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
		<pb n="2"/>
			<p rend="align(right)"><date>Monday&#44; 8<hi rend="sup">th</hi> of Shevat&#44; 1854</date></p>
			<p rend="align(right)">&#40;<date>February</date>&#41;</p>
			<p>Most treasured friend&#58;</p>
          <p rend="indent(1)">I have no doubt you received my<lb/> last letter with the enclosed &#36;3. of <persName>Isaac Gersom</persName><lb/> &#42; and if it is not worth anything&#44; I am returning<lb/> the receipt to you. I have already spoken with<lb/> <persName>Marx</persName>&#44; and he promised to send it up to now&#44;<lb/> he hasn&#39;t sent me even a stone. I think you<lb/> would be doing well to send a reminder to<lb/> both these gentlemen to send me the money. I<lb/> have also told you that you could set aside<lb/> several of your school books. The money for<lb/> those which you sent to <persName>Bruger</persName> <add>&#63;</add>&#44; you will<lb/> receive at the beginning of next month. I am<lb/> enclosing a letter to <persName>Dr. Lilienthal</persName>&#44; which I ask<lb/> you to translate into English. My intention<lb/> and hope is only for the glory of God&#8212;to prove<lb/> through this letter the necessity for the second day<lb/> of the holidays. I positively request that you<lb/> permit it to appear this month. I have already<lb/> <del>sent</del> prepared an answer for him to his heretical questions&#44;<lb/> that is to all the questions he directed to you. I<lb/> expect your answer by return mail.</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)">Most respectfully&#44;</p>
          <p rend="indent(8)"><persName role="author">Dr. Illoway</persName>.</p>
			<p>&#42;Perhaps he thinks the<lb/> check is worthless.</p>
          
        </body>
